<subSubSection id="A2D3C1A9FF9C3847FF75D30FFC14AA85" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF9C3847FF75D30FFC14AA85" blockId="6.[151,1437,258,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9C3847FF75D30FFE86AA19" bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing light brown, subhyaline; wing with obviously white net-like lines; Rs straight, as long as r-m; base of halter dark brown, apex of haltere black. Epandrium semicircular, lateral and posterior margin rounded, posterior margin slightly concaved medially; cercus transverse, bilobate, each lobe elliptical; outer gonostylus forming a broad semicircular lobe medially, apical part finger-like.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A2D3C1A9FF9C3846FF25D39FFE35AECF" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="428" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" type="description">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF9C3847FF25D39FFD89A9C9" blockId="6.[151,1437,258,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9C3847FF25D39FFE08AAA9" bold="true" box="[199,415,402,427]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Description. Male</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity id="2D313FC7FF9C3847FDABD39EFD32AAA8" box="[585,677,403,427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="2D313FC7FF9C3847FCA5D39FFC34AAA8" box="[839,931,402,427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
, wing width 
<quantity id="2D313FC7FF9C3847FBDDD39EFB0BAAA8" box="[1087,1180,403,427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
. Head uniformly dark brown. Ocellar triangle dark brown. Eyes with a row of several long hairs along dorsal margin; vertex with two bunches of long hairs. Compound eyes dichoptic, boundary of upper division and lower division conspicuous; upper division of eye about 
<number id="5C018005FF9C3847FE35D3F2FE76A915" box="[471,481,511,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="5C018005FF9C3847FE09D3F2FE6CA915" box="[491,507,511,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" value="2.0">2</number>
as large as lower division; brick-red with pubescences; lower division black with pubescences. Ocelli large, light yellow, prominent. Antenna longer than head width; scape and pedicel short; flagellomeres 
<number id="5C018005FF9C3847FEDAD04AFEE7A95D" box="[312,368,583,607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" value="6.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="1.0">1–12</number>
mostly subequal in length, twice longer than wide; antenna uniformly dark brown with short black hairs. Proboscis shorter than height of head, with short black hairs. Palpus five-segmented, first segment short, 
<number id="5C018005FF9C3847FF3CD083FF7CA9A5" box="[222,235,654,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" value="2.0">2</number>
nd– 
<number id="5C018005FF9C3847FEF4D083FEB4A9A5" box="[278,291,654,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" value="4.0">4</number>
th segments long, fifth segment slender and long, as long as the total length of segments 
<number id="5C018005FF9C3847FAFBD082FAD1A9A5" box="[1305,1350,655,679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
; palpus brown, with uniformly black hairs.
</paragraph>
<caption id="BEB6C2AAFF9C3847FF75D584FAF6ACA2" box="[151,1377,1929,1952]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226449/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" targetBox="[362,1222,776,1908]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF9C3847FF75D584FAF6ACA2" blockId="6.[151,1377,1929,1952]" box="[151,1377,1929,1952]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9C3847FF75D584FEC4AC9D" bold="true" box="[151,339,1929,1952]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">FIGURES 12–13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2DC9E9A1FF9C3847FEB8D587FDAFACA2" box="[346,568,1930,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Blepharicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9C3847FEB8D587FDAFACA2" box="[346,568,1930,1952]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Blepharicera hainana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C38EF34BFF9C3847FDDDD587FD1DAC9D" box="[575,650,1930,1951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" rank="species">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9C3847FDDDD587FD1DAC9D" bold="true" box="[575,650,1930,1951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">sp.nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 12: Habitus of male, lateral view; 13: Wing. Scale bar: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="BEB6C2AAFF9D3846FF75D1E6FEA8AF22" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226450/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" targetBox="[157,1429,199,978]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF9D3846FF75D1E6FEA8AF22" blockId="7.[151,1436,1003,1056]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9D3846FF75D1E6FEC0AF02" bold="true" box="[151,343,1003,1026]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">FIGURES 14–15.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2DC9E9A1FF9D3846FE82D1E6FDD5AF03" box="[352,578,1003,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Blepharicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9D3846FE82D1E6FDD5AF03" box="[352,578,1003,1025]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">Blepharicera hainana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C38EF34BFF9D3846FDAED1E1FD01AF03" box="[588,662,1004,1025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" rank="species">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9D3846FDAED1E1FD01AF03" bold="true" box="[588,662,1004,1025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">sp.nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 14: Genitalia, dorsal view. 15: Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bar: 14–15= 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="EA769222FF9D3846FF25D641FECFAFD3" blockId="7.[151,1437,1100,1809]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
Thoracic dorsum uniformly dark brown; pleuron brown; thorax without hairs. Legs brown, hairs on legs black. Wing (
<figureCitation id="72F28EA7FF9D3846FF01D67DFEA4AF8B" box="[227,307,1136,1161]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1929,1952]" captionTargetBox="[362,1222,776,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[348,1238,767,1908]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 13. Blepharicera hainana sp. nov. (male). 12: Habitus of male, lateral view; 13: Wing. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226449/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
Fig. 
<number id="5C018005FF9D3846FEF5D67CFEA4AF8B" box="[279,307,1137,1161]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) light brown, subhyaline; wing with obviously white net-like lines, veins brown. Sc rudimentary, not ending at base of Rs; Rs straight, as long as r-m; r-m straight. Base of halter dark brown, apex of halter black, with short black hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA769222FF9D3846FF32D6D1FB4EAEAA" blockId="7.[151,1437,1100,1809]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
Abdominal tergites mainly dark brown, tergites 
<number id="5C018005FF9D3846FD1AD6D1FCB5AFF7" box="[760,802,1244,1269]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
with narrow yellow brown band basally, sternites dark brown; hairs on abdomen black. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="72F28EA7FF9D3846FD50D70DFCACAE1B" box="[690,827,1280,1305]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1003,1026]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,199,978]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,982]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 15. Blepharicera hainana sp. nov. (male). 14: Genitalia, dorsal view. 15: Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bar: 14 – 15 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226450/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
Figs. 
<number id="5C018005FF9D3846FD13D70DFCACAE1B" box="[753,827,1280,1305]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
</figureCitation>
): Epandrium semicircular, lateral and posterior margin rounded, posterior margin slightly concaved medially, with uniformly short hairs; hypandrium trapezoidal, posterior margin wavy, slightly concave medially, with short hairs laterally; cercus transverse, bilobate, each lobe elliptical, with dense patch of hairs apically; outer gonostylus forming a broad semicircular lobe medially, apical part finger-like, with uniformly hairs; inner gonostylus slender and curved; paramere transparent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA769222FF9D3846FF25D7B9FE35AECF" blockId="7.[151,1437,1100,1809]" box="[199,418,1460,1485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9D3846FF25D7B9FE89AECF" bold="true" box="[199,286,1460,1485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
